65: /**
66:  * A pending checkpoint is a checkpoint that has been started, but has not been acknowledged by all
67:  * tasks that need to acknowledge it. Once all tasks have acknowledged it, it becomes a {@link
68:  * CompletedCheckpoint}.
69:  *
70:  * <p>Note that the pending checkpoint, as well as the successful checkpoint keep the state handles
71:  * always as serialized values, never as actual values.
72:  */
