128: /**
129:  * The Task represents one execution of a parallel subtask on a TaskManager. A Task wraps a Flink
130:  * operator (which may be a user function) and runs it, providing all services necessary for example
131:  * to consume input data, produce its results (intermediate result partitions) and communicate with
132:  * the JobManager.
133:  *
134:  * <p>The Flink operators (implemented as subclasses of {@link TaskInvokable} have only data
135:  * readers, writers, and certain event callbacks. The task connects those to the network stack and
136:  * actor messages, and tracks the state of the execution and handles exceptions.
137:  *
138:  * <p>Tasks have no knowledge about how they relate to other tasks, or whether they are the first
139:  * attempt to execute the task, or a repeated attempt. All of that is only known to the JobManager.
140:  * All the task knows are its own runnable code, the task's configuration, and the IDs of the
141:  * intermediate results to consume and produce (if any).
142:  *
143:  * <p>Each Task is run by one dedicated thread.
144:  */
